</TEXT></Q>
<P><HI>Which Report is approved by this Court, and</HI> Ordered, <HI>That the Freedom and Box be forthwith made, pur&s;uant to the &s;aid Report, and that Mr.</HI> Sharpas, <HI>the Common Clerk of this City, do affix the Seal to the &s;ame Freedom, and inclo&s;e it in the &s;aid Box.</HI></P>
<P>Mr. Alderman <HI>Bayard going to</HI> Philadelphia <HI>and offering to be the Bearer of the &s;aid Freedom to Mr.</HI> Hamilton, Ordered, <HI>That Mr.</HI> Sharpas <HI>deliver it to Alderman</HI> Bayard <HI>for that Purpo&s;e; and that Alderman</HI> Bayard <HI>do deliver it to Mr.</HI> Hamilton, <HI>with A&s;&s;urances of the great E&s;teem, that this Corporation have for his Per&s;on and Merit.</HI></P>
</DIV2>
