<Q><TEXT LANG="eng">
<BODY>
<DIV1 TYPE="order">
<P>Ordered, <HI>That the Freedom, granted by this Corporation, to</HI> Andrew Hamilton, <HI><ABBR>E&s;q</ABBR> with the Report of the Committee, for preparing a Draught of the &s;ame and the Order of this Court, thereon, may be printed.</HI></P>
<CLOSER><SIGNED>William Sharpas.</SIGNED></CLOSER>
</DIV1>
</BODY>
</TEXT></Q>
<P>Round on the Lid of the Box mentioned in the above&s;aid Report and Order, there is ingraved not only the Arms of the City of <HI>New-York,</HI> but al&s;o this Motto in a Garter;
<Q>DEMERSAE LEGES-TIMEFACTA LIBERTAS-HAEC TANDEM EMERGUNT.</Q></P>
<P>On the inner Side of the Lid of the Box &s;hewing it &s;elf at the &s;ame Time with the Certificate of the Freedom; There is Engraven in a flying Garter, the&s;e Words.</P>
<Q>NON NUMMIS, &mdash; VIRTUTE PARATUR.</Q>
<P>As an Incentive to publick Virtue, on the Front of the Rim of the &s;aid Box, there is engraven a Part of <HI>Tully's</HI> Wi&s;h;
<Q>ITA CUIQUE EVENIAT, UT DE REPUBLICA VERUIT</Q></P>
<P>Which Freedom and Box was pre&s;ented in the Manner that had been directed, and gratefully accepted by the &s;aid <HI>Andrew Hamilton,</HI> <ABBR>E&s;q</ABBR></P>
